OL,3,CVisually impaired mum told she 'should
OL,4,Cnot have kids' in disability hate crime
OL,6,FIn just one year more than 13,000
OL,7,Freports of disability hate crime were
OL,8,Fmade, but only around 1% resulted in a
OL,9,Fcriminal charge, according to
OL,10,Fgovernment statistics across England
OL,11,Fand Wales in 2022-2023.
OL,13,FJessica Tait, Policy Manager at
OL,14,FDisability Positive, said: "It ends up
OL,15,Fbeing a situation where they don't
OL,16,Ffeel they have a community of support
OL,17,Fbehind them, so they don't want to
OL,18,Freport what's happening to them.
OL,20,F"They perhaps don't realise that they
OL,21,Fhave the option to do that."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/7
